headline: Rio Tinto to supply copper to Amazon for AI data centers
summary: Rio Tinto said on Thursday it would supply copper that it leaches from an Arizona mine to Amazon.com ​for use in the tech giant's artificial intelligence data centers.  The ‌move underscores the rampant push by the AI industry for access to supplies of copper ‌and other critical minerals that are used to build wiring, cables, circuit boards and other electronic parts.  AI sector growth is expected to boost global copper demand 50% by 2040, although analysts have warned supplies could fall far ⁠short, sparking a rush to ‌ensure access.
